trans-unit.source: Represents a single relationship between an object and a member.
<xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.MemberRelationshipService> is used by a serializer to announce that one property is related to a property on another object.

MemberRelationship represents a single relationship between an object and a member that <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.MemberRelationshipService> uses in its interactions with a serializer.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.MemberRelationship"></xref> class.
The object that owns `member`.
The member which is to be related to `owner`.

A <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.MemberRelationship> structure is empty if neither the owner nor the member is assigned.
